# Deployment Hardening

Deviations are bugs, not preferences.

## Deployment targets

Primary: Railway (backend) + Vercel (frontend) + Supabase (auth + Postgres).
Alternative: Self-hosted via `docker-compose.yml` (VPS with nginx/certbot).

There are three environments: `development`, `test`, `production`. There is no staging.

## Railway
- Deployed via `railway.toml` (Dockerfile builder). `docker-compose.yml` is NOT used on Railway.
- Railway auto-sets `PORT` — the Dockerfile CMD uses `${PORT:-8000}`.
- Env vars are set in Railway dashboard > Settings > Variables. See `deploy/railway-env.example`.
- `DATABASE_URL` must use Supabase **direct** connection (port 5432), NOT the pooler (port 6543). asyncpg prepared statements are incompatible with pgbouncer.
- `JWT_SECRET` must be the Supabase project's JWT secret — not a random value.
- `CORS_ORIGINS` must include all stable Vercel domains. `CORS_ORIGIN_REGEX` can match preview deploys.
- `FRONTEND_URL` needed for Xero OAuth redirects.
- Health check: `GET /api/health` (configured in `railway.toml`).

## Vercel
- Root `vercel.json` controls monorepo build: `cd frontend && npm ci && npm run build`.
- Output: `frontend/dist`. SPA rewrite: all routes → `index.html`.
- Three `VITE_*` env vars are build-time (baked into JS). Changing requires redeploy.
- Security headers set in `vercel.json`: `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`.
- Immutable cache headers on `/assets/`.

## Docker
- Two-stage build: `builder` (compilers, uv sync) → `runtime` (venv only, no headers)
- Non-root: `appuser:appgroup` uid/gid 1001, `USER appuser` before `CMD`
- `ENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1` in runtime stage — required for log streaming
- `CMD` calls `uvicorn` directly via activated venv. No `uv run` wrapper in production.
- `devtools/` never copied into image

## nginx (VPS path only)
- `keepalive 32` on upstream; all proxy locations use `proxy_http_version 1.1` + `Connection ""`
- API timeouts: `proxy_connect_timeout 5s`, `proxy_send_timeout 30s`, `proxy_read_timeout 120s`
- WebSocket timeouts: `proxy_read_timeout 3600s`, `proxy_send_timeout 3600s`
- Rate zones: `api` 60r/m, `auth` 10r/m, `chat` 20r/m — all in nginx, none in Python
- `proxy_set_header X-Request-ID $request_id` on every proxy location — required for log correlation
- HSTS, `X-Content-Type-Options nosniff`, `X-Frame-Options DENY`, `Referrer-Policy strict-origin-when-cross-origin`
- `/metrics` restricted to loopback + RFC1918 only

## CORS
`_enforce_cors()` in `config.py` hard-crashes at startup if `CORS_ORIGINS` is `"*"` or empty in production. Not a warning.
`CORS_ORIGIN_REGEX` is applied in addition to `CORS_ORIGINS` — useful for Vercel preview deploy URLs.

## Connection pool
`PG_POOL_MAX` per worker × `WORKERS` = total Postgres connections. Size accordingly. `PG_ACQUIRE_TIMEOUT` (default 10s) is the starvation circuit-breaker — requests 503 rather than queue. `PG_COMMAND_TIMEOUT` (default 30s) kills runaway queries.

## Auth
- Tokens without `organization_id` → 401/4001 at transport layer in production
- `JWT_SECRET` must be set and not the dev default in production — startup crashes otherwise
- For Supabase: `JWT_SECRET` must be the Supabase project's JWT secret (Dashboard > Settings > API)
- Provider is auto-selected: supabase in production, internal in dev/test. Claim extraction lives only in `shared/api/auth_provider.py`

## Health probes
- `/api/health` — liveness, never blocks on DB, must complete < 100ms
- `/api/ready` — readiness, checks DB pool. Load balancers gate traffic on this, not `/api/health`

## Observability
- `SENTRY_DSN` should be set in production. Do not suppress exceptions to reduce Sentry noise — fix the underlying issue.
- Application logs are JSON (configured in `shared/infrastructure/logging_config.py`). Every log line within a request carries `request_id` from the `X-Request-ID` propagation middleware.

## Required production env vars (Railway)
```
ENV=production
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...          # Supabase direct, port 5432
JWT_SECRET=<supabase-jwt-secret>       # Must match Supabase project
CORS_ORIGINS=https://your.vercel.app   # All stable Vercel domains
REDIS_URL=redis://...                  # Required if WORKERS > 1
FRONTEND_URL=https://your.vercel.app   # For OAuth redirects
WORKERS=1                              # Increase with Redis
```

## Required production env vars (Vercel)
```
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://your.railway.app
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxx.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
```
